HEADWORD: Berna fly
<hw>Ber"na fly`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A Brazilian
dipterous insect of the genus <gen>Trypeta</gen>, which lays its eggs in
the nostrils or in wounds of man and beast, where the larv⟦ae⟧ do great
injury.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bernardine</ent>⟦br⟧
